cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with LDPC codes and their decoding over a binary memoryless channel, which is a topic closely related to information theory.
2. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the performance of belief-propagation decoding of SC-LDPC codes, which involves computational complexity.
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper may be relevant to networking and internet architecture as LDPC codes are commonly used in communication systems.
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper may be relevant to social and information networks as LDPC codes are used in distributed storage systems and network coding.
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the decoding failure probability of SC-LDPC codes, which may involve data structures and algorithms.
